== Drive Reversal ==
[[File:SF6_drive_reversal.jpg|thumb|250px|"Perform a counterattack while blocking an opponent’s attack. The damage is low but can help you out of tight situations when you’re being pressured." - ''Capcom.'']]
<br>
'''Costs 2 Drive Stocks.''' Press {{f}}+{{hp sf6}}+{{hk sf6}} ({{clr|H|6HPHK}}) during blockstun to perform. 
{| class="wikitable"
! Startup !! Active !! Recovery !! Damage !! On Hit !! On Block !!
|- style="text-align: center"
| 20(18) || 3 || 26(31)* || 500 (rec) || KD +23* || -6
|}

<small>''- 18f startup is for Recovery Drive Reversal (explained below).''</small><br>
<small>''- Recovery is increased by 5f on hit (6f for Dhalsim, 7f for Chun-Li).''</small><br>
<small>''- Advantage on hit is +24 for Dhalsim.''</small><br>
<small>''- Chun-Li and Dhalsim have 2-hit Drive Reversals, with active frames 3(10)3 and 3(6)3 respectively.''</small><br>
<small>''- Alex and Marisa have 4f less hitstop on blocked Drive Reversal, which shifts the punish timing to be earlier than usual.''</small>
<br><br>
Drive Reversal '''(DRev)''' is similar to Alpha Counter or V-Reversal from previous Street Fighter games, being used to counterattack from blockstun after an opponent's attack.

Drive Reversal is fully invincible throughout all of its startup and active frames, and deals a small amount of recoverable damage on hit. Drive Reversals have the Armor Break property, so you don't have to worry about things like the opponent canceling into Drive Impact to counter your Drive Reversal.

All Drive Reversals are punishable at {{sf6-adv|VM|-6}} on block, and are slow enough that quick attacks will recover before the Drive Reversal connects. DRev immediately ends the blockstun of the opponent's attack, so inputting it earlier increases the chance of successfully punishing the opponent's move. The blockstun of a successful Parry can also be canceled with Drive Reversal, and this is the only way to use it against Drive Impact. It is impossible to win a round with the damage from Drive Reversal.

There is a short 4-frame screen freeze that occurs after the 6th startup frame of Drive Reversal out of blockstun (but not on wakeup). In addition to making it slightly more reactable to the attacker, this can also prevent the 2nd attack of a blockstring from coming out. For example, when inputting Kimberly's {{clr|M|2MP}}, {{clr|M|5MP}} with its usual combo timing against an immediate Drive Reversal, the screen freeze would cause {{clr|M|5MP}} to be input too early, preventing it from being buffered. However, if the Drive Reversal is delayed a few frames, the {{clr|M|5MP}} would have already been buffered before the freeze. 

One of the strongest uses for Drive Reversal may be to prevent the opponent's corner escape; if they try to force some offense to push you back, simply knock them back into the corner for 2 Drive bars. It's important to learn which of the opponent's moves recovery quickly enough to block DRev, however, or you may end up getting punished and cornered yourself. DRev can also be used to punish a blocked normal canceled into {{clr|DR|Drive Rush}}; the opponent would have to predict your DRev and use a delayed invincible move to avoid it.

=== Recovery Drive Reversal ===
'''Costs 2 Drive Stocks.''' Press '''(or hold)''' {{f}}+{{hp sf6}}+{{hk sf6}} ({{clr|H|6HPHK}}) during the recovery from a knockdown to perform. 

As the name suggests, Recovery Drive Reversal is a special version of Drive Reversal performed while recovering from a knockdown (aka. on wakeup). Compared to Drive Reversal out of blockstun, this version (also called "Wake-up Drive Reversal", "RDRev", etc.) '''starts up 2 frames faster (18f)''', though the rest of its frame data is the same. It does, however, have a few other special properties.

'''During your wake-up, you can hold the input to guarantee that it will come out as a reversal, without any risk of mistiming it.'''

Additionally, if an opponent attempts to throw you during the invincibility of your Recovery Drive Reversal, a short 12f screen freeze with a special visual effect will be triggered, and a Punish Counter message will be displayed on screen as the opponent gets knocked down.

'''While this Punish Counter against an incoming throw won't drain the opponent's Drive Gauge, it will refund you 1 Drive bar.'''

This won't prevent you from entering Burnout, but it will fill up the equivalent amount of the Burnout Drive Gauge as well. This makes it easier to defend against corner throw loops without putting yourself into a poor meter position.

